name: #1 POSTCARD FROM BUENOS AIRES
description:
On the back of each postcard, I have been writing messages that I wanted to express to the people that every day sees my work.

This one is the only one that I kept for me, once I sold out I didn't print it again. 
With printing mistakes is the honest and sincere way to show my work. I have never been the best photographer, I always focused on being REAL. So, every mistake is a way to show my learning journey. 

I wrote this as a prediction of my way.
I always knew that my last stop traveling would be my home.
